Ninja Video Downloader

Ninja Video Downloader is a simple tool for downloading videos from TikTok and YouTube using yt-dlp. This tool automatically handles the installation of yt-dlp, creates a designated download directory, and logs all download activities.

Features

- Downloads videos from TikTok and YouTube.
- Automatically installs yt-dlp if not present.
- Logs download activities to a log file.
- Outputs downloaded videos to a specified directory.

Installation

1. Clone this repository:
   git clone https://github.com/yourusername/NinjaVideoDownloader.git

2. Navigate to the directory:
   cd NinjaVideoDownloader

3. Run the PowerShell script:
   .\NinjaVideoDownloader.ps1

Usage

1. Run the PowerShell script.
2. When prompted, enter the URL of the TikTok or YouTube video you want to download.
3. The video will be downloaded to C:\Program Files\NinjaVideoDownloader.

Logging

All activities are logged to C:\Program Files\NinjaVideoDownloader\NinjaVideoDownloader.log. Check this file for detailed output on the download process.

Requirements

- Windows operating system
- PowerShell

Troubleshooting

- If you encounter issues, ensure you have the necessary permissions to write to the download directory.
- Check the log file for error messages to diagnose problems.

